ften. Mit diesem Buch bereitet Anabel Ternès von Hattburg die Grundlage für ein neues Orientierungsmodell, das im digitalen Wandel Halt geben kann und auf Transparenz sowie einer kritischen Hinterfragung basiert.  aThe digital transformation poses challenges for everyone. From smart homes to the flood of online information when looking for even the most basic of products – people today need new sources of orientation and must decide on whom to trust for guidance. This book presents approaches for finding one’s bearing and discusses a new model that takes into account the effects of the digital change on people’s lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aDigitales Zeitalter. 4aDigitalisierung. 4aMensch 4.0. 4aOrientierung im digitalen Wandel. 4aTransformation. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW0 cEPUBz97831106445170 cprintz978311064444940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311064445640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110644456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110644456.jpg  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DSWb2019